stable measurement (this session's re-run: p95 1,643.87ms, min 1,093.57ms, median 1,385.42ms -- comfortably under 3,000ms and consistent with debug-notes' own stable-sample figures). Remaining residual gap: only 10 samples in this run (smoke-sized, single concurrency=1 client) -- a wider/longer soak or concurrent-client load run would build more confidence in production but is not required by the confirmed AC wording.\",\n20\t        \"severity\": \"low\"\n21\t      },\n22\t      {\n23\t        \"area\": \"AC9 streaming-not-buffered\",\n24\t        \"gap\": \"The chunk-count>1 assertion is a reasonable proxy for 'not fully buffered' but does not directly measure peak memory. A future regression that buffers the whole result client-side but still happens to flush in more than one TCP segment (e.g. due to buffering N rows at a time rather than 1) would still pass this test. A memory-ceiling assertion (e.g. tracemalloc peak during the stream) would close this more tightly.\",\n25\t        \"severity\": \"medium\"\n26\t      },\n27\t      {\n28\t        \"area\": \"usage_repo.py count_usage_rollups / stream_usage_rollups\",\n29\t        \"gap\": \"No test exercises a combination of ALL four filters simultaneously (customer_id + metric + from + to together) -- each filter is tested in isolation. The shared `_export_filter_clause_and_params` helper makes this low-risk (the WHERE-clause construction is compositional and unit-testable by inspection), but an integration test combining all four would remove the remaining inference.\",\n30\t        \"severity\": \"low\"\n31\t      },\n32\t      {\n33\t        \"area\": \"usage_export_service.py stream_export_csv\",\n34\t        \"gap\": \"No test drives a client disconnect mid-stream against the real integration server (running_server fixture) to observe the `completed=False` log path under real ASGI/ASGI-middleware conditions -- the unit test simulates this by raising inside a mocked generator, which proves the finally-block logic but not that Starlette's real disconnect handling reaches it the same way in production.\",\n35\t        \"severity\": \"low\"\n36\t      },\n37\t      {\n38\t        \"area\": \"usage_repo.py line 130 (count_usage_rollups' `return result.scalar_one()`)\",\n39\t        \"gap\": \"Coverage reports this exact line as missed despite count_usage_rollups being called by many passing tests (cap-boundary, cap-exceeded, filter tests) -- worth a follow-up look (likely a coverage/line-mapping artifact from the f-string SQL literal spanning multiple source lines, not a real untested branch, but not independently confirmed this session).\",\n40\t        \"severity\": \"low\"\n41\t      }\n42\t    ]\n43\t  }\n44\t}\n45\t"}]},"uuid":"9ccfe050-a1e9-4438-b6ee-dd24b4dbc6b1","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:35:01.803Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c86c7284-6f49-40d8-886d-8e3f56c00a6d","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
