{"parentUuid":"62b6f497-053b-407d-acfa-0cdcd8451d53","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DbmTf2bBe1Qp6PbxjZSJCK","type":"tool_result","content":"diff --git a/.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml b/.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml\nindex 600d34e..99912a9 100644\n--- a/.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml\n+++ b/.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml\n@@ -63,10 +63,11 @@ jobs:\n       - name: Build\n         run: poetry run python -c \"import src.main\"\n       - name: Test with coverage (floor = the local gate's figure)\n-        run: poetry run pytest --cov=src --cov-branch\n-        # Fail under <COVERAGE_FLOOR>% combined lines — the same figure the local deploy\n-        # gate rides. Branch coverage: surface in the job summary, do NOT gate (mirrors\n-        # the local posture; see test-conventions).\n+        run: poetry run pytest --cov=src --cov-branch --cov-fail-under=85\n+        # Fail under 85% combined lines — CLAUDE.md's done-bar figure (\"tests pass at\n+        # >= 85% coverage\"), the same figure the local deploy gate rides. Branch\n+        # coverage: surface in the job summary, do NOT gate (mirrors the local\n+        # posture; see test-conventions).\n \n   # mutation — U-22: run mutation testing HERE, on the Linux runner, not on the author's\n   # host. mutmut needs a POSIX environment (WSL on Windows), so the local pipeline honestly\ndiff --git a/PROJECT.md b/PROJECT.md\nindex ef22d91..bc052b4 100644\n--- a/PROJECT.md\n+++ b/PROJECT.md\n@@ -1,6 +1,4 @@\n-Feature: per-customer metric quotas.\n-- PUT /v1/quotas (admin-scoped API key) sets {customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}.\n-- POST /v1/events returns 429 with a quota error envelope when the current-window rollup for that customer/metric would exceed the quota. Customers without a quota are unlimited (no behavior change).\n-- One expand-only migration: a quotas table.\n-- Existing perf budget applies: p95 < 50 ms under load on POST /v1/events.\n+Feature: usage CSV export.\n+- GET /v1/usage/export returns the caller's usage rollups (customer_id, metric, window_start, total_quantity) as CSV.\n+- Existing API-key auth applies. No behavior change to any existing endpoint.\n Design source: none.\ndiff --git a/src/main.py b/src/main.py\nindex 1215395..624b911 100644\n--- a/src/main.py\n+++ b/src/main.py\n@@ -29,6 +29,7 @@ from src.api.routes.events import router as events_router\n from src.api.routes.health import router as health_router\n from src.api.routes.quotas import router as quotas_router\n from src.api.routes.usage import router as usage_router\n+from src.api.routes.usage_export import router as usage_export_router\n from src.config.settings import get_settings\n from src.db.session import dispose_engine\n from src.logging import get_logger\n@@ -85,6 +86,7 @@ def create_app() -> FastAPI:\n     app.include_router(health_router)\n     app.include_router(events_router)\n     app.include_router(usage_router)\n+    app.include_router(usage_export_router)\n     app.include_router(quotas_router)\n \n     # Must run after routes are mounted (FastAPIInstrumentor introspects them)","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"6f9c5e08-64b2-4ce6-a5ad-865ec3b7dca8","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:35:36.844Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"62b6f497-053b-407d-acfa-0cdcd8451d53","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"6f9c5e08-64b2-4ce6-a5ad-865ec3b7dca8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs89fj6PVC5zPAtm8VnU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BACpnXMux4pTKBKXJGPFK6","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\debug-notes.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7429,"cache_read_input_tokens":72566,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7429,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs89dwgseqGEKiHjLCNk","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"ccf71612-0c92-4549-9df9-c6b5448b534a","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:35:36.945Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"ccf71612-0c92-4549-9df9-c6b5448b534a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BACpnXMux4pTKBKXJGPFK6","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Debug notes — GET /v1/usage/export\n2\t\n3\t## 2026-07-09 — AC16 export p95 blow-up at the 100,000-row cap (remediation)\n4\t\n5\t### Finding (testing gate, AC16)\n6\t`GET /v1/usage/export` p95 at the 100k-row cap measured **25,210 ms** (testing's\n7\tindependent re-measure) / earlier **~9.8 s** (implementation's measure) against\n8\tthe plan's **proposed 500 ms** target — 20–50x over. Implementation's disclosure\n9\tattributed it to \"per-row Python CSV encoding overhead, not DB time\".\n10\t\n11\t### Reproduced first (before touching anything)\n12\tRan `tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` (real Postgres testcontainer,\n13\tin-process ASGI, 100,000 rows). Baseline p95 this session (the test's scratch\n14\tmeasurement file): **10,720.92 ms**, `meets_documented_budget: false`. Reproduced.\n15\t(The gap vs testing's 25,210 ms is host load/hardware; both are 20–50x over.)\n16\t\n17\t### Root cause — measured, not assumed (the disclosure was only partly right)\n18\tI profiled each layer of the path in isolation (scratch benchmarks, 100k rows):\n19\t\n20\t| Layer measured in isolation | time |\n21\t|---|---|\n22\t| Pure CSV encoding (escape+format+writerow, no I/O) | ~360 ms |\n23\t| ...of which `escape_csv_text_cell`'s per-char generator + `_is_safe_character` + `ord()` | ~2.4M genexpr / 2.2M `ord` calls — the encoding hot spot |\n24\t| Real `stream_export_csv` async generator consumed directly (fake in-mem DB) | ~387 ms |\n25\t| Through a **bare** StreamingResponse + ASGITransport (no middleware, fake DB) | ~441 ms |\n26\t| Real DB server-side cursor draining 100k rows (no CSV, no HTTP), default fetch | ~1,014 ms |\n27\t| ...same, with `yield_per=5000` | ~609 ms |\n28\t| Full real `stream_export_csv` on the real DB, **minimal** Starlette app (no middleware) | ~1,644 ms |\n29\t| ...the same path with **4 nested pass-through `BaseHTTPMiddleware`** layers added | **~6,944 ms** |\n30\t\n31\tThe server-side `request.completed` log confirmed the handler *returns* in 16–94 ms;\n32\tthe ~10 s is spent **after** the handler returns, in the streaming phase.\n33\t\n34\t**The dominant cost is the CHUNK-PER-ROW streaming pattern, not encoding.** The\n35\tgenerator did `yield _drain(buffer)` **per row** → 100,001 chunks at the cap. The\n36\tapp stack (`src/main.py`) has **four nested Starlette `BaseHTTPMiddleware`**\n37\tsubclasses (`RequestContextMiddleware`, `SecurityHeadersMiddleware`,\n38\t`BodySizeLimitMiddleware`, `Tier1EdgeThrottleMiddleware`).\n39\t`BaseHTTPMiddleware` re-pumps **every** streamed chunk through its own anyio\n40\tmemory-object-stream; with 4 nested layers, all 100k tiny chunks traverse 4\n41\tanyio hops each, with async scheduling per hop. Cost ≈ (chunk count × middleware\n42\tlayers), so it exploded at the cap. Encoding (~360 ms) and DB drain (~1 s) were\n43\tsecondary. The implementation's disclosure conflated the fast COUNT + bounded\n44\tsort (genuinely fast) with the row-*drain* + per-chunk-fan-out cost.\n45\t\n46\t### Fix — minimal, localized, WITHIN the human-approved design\n47\tServer-side cursor, pre-flight COUNT, 100k cap, and OWASP formula-escape\n48\tsemantics all preserved. Three complementary in-scope optimizations:\n49\t\n50\t1. **`src/services/usage_export_service.py` — batch rows per chunk** (`_ROWS_PER_CHUNK\n51\t   = 1000`) instead of one chunk per row. Header still yielded first as its own\n52\t   chunk (AC12 empty-result / AC9 first-bytes). At the cap this is ~101 chunks,\n53\t   not 100,001 — still genuinely streamed, still constant memory (buffer holds ≤\n54\t   one batch). **Primary lever.**\n55\t2. **`src/api/csv_export.py` — precompiled escape.** Replaced the per-character\n56\t   Python strip loop in `escape_csv_text_cell` with a C-level `str.translate`\n57\t   deletion table. Semantics **identical** (verified 0 mismatches across all\n58\t   codepoints 0x00–0x11F and lead/mid combos vs. the old logic, and by the\n59\t   unchanged AC10 tests). Encoding 360 → 246 ms.\n60\t3. **`src/repositories/usage_repo.py` — `yield_per=5000`** on the `session.stream()`\n61\t   server-side cursor. Tunes how many rows are fetched per round-trip; does NOT\n62\t   abandon the cursor. Controlled tight-loop DB drain 1,014 → 609 ms; memory\n63\t   still bounded (≤ one batch buffered client-side).\n64\t\n65\t### Proven\n66\t- **Regression test (fails-before / passes-after):**\n67\t  `tests/test_usage_export_service.py::test_stream_export_csv_batches_rows_into_few_chunks`\n68\t  — a 5,000-row export must arrive in < 500 chunks (batched) **and** > 1 chunk\n69\t  (still streamed), with byte-identical CSV. Per-row impl produced 5,001 chunks\n70\t  (**fails**); batched impl produces 6 (**passes**). Fails-before confirmed via a\n71\t  scratch reproduction of the per-row logic (real tree never reverted);\n72\t  passes-after **12/12** consecutive runs (deterministic, no DB/timing).\n73\t- **No suite regressions:** `test_csv_export.py` + `test_usage_export_service.py`\n74\t  + `test_schemas_usage_export.py` = **37 passed**; `test_usage_export_endpoint.py`\n75\t  + `test_usage_export_perf.py` = **20 passed** (AC2/AC5–AC13/AC17/AC19/AC20/AC22\n76\t  incl. AC9 streaming-multiple-chunks and AC10 formula-escape all green with\n77\t  batching + the escape refactor).\n78\t\n79\t### Before / after p95 at the 100,000-row cap (real perf test, full app stack)\n80\t- **BEFORE:** 10,720.92 ms (this session) / 25,210 ms (testing's independent measure)\n81\t- **AFTER (all 3 opts):** ~1.4 s median, ~2.0 s p95 — the 2-sample perf test\n82\t  recorded 1,454.93 ms (batching+escape) and 2,042.80 ms (all 3); a stable\n83\t  10-sample re-measure through a 4-`BaseHTTPMiddleware` stack gave\n84\t  **min 1,139 ms / median 1,374 ms / p95 2,073 ms**. Net: **~7–17x faster**, and\n85\t  the chunk-per-row anti-pattern is eliminated.\n86\t\n87\t### Best achieved STILL exceeds 500 ms — budget decision escalates to the human\n88\tEven after this genuine optimization pass, p95 (~1.4–2.0 s) remains above the\n89\tplan's **proposed** 500 ms. The remainder is dominated by **irreducible work\n90\twithin the approved design**:\n91\t- Draining 100k rows over the async **server-side cursor**: ~0.6 s even at\n92\t  `yield_per=5000`. A buffered `fetchall` (which would ABANDON the mandated\n93\t  constant-memory cursor) was ~0.32 s — so the cursor floor is already ≥0.6 s.\n94\t- Python-level CSV encoding of 100k rows × 4 cells: ~0.25 s.\n95\t- Even the theoretical floor that DISCARDS the cursor (fetchall 0.32 s + encoding\n96\t  0.25 s ≈ 0.57 s) is already over 500 ms; with the mandated cursor it is ~0.85–1.0 s.\n97\t\n98\t**500 ms is not achievable at the 100k-row cap within the approved design**\n99\t(server-side cursor + per-row stdlib `csv` + streaming through the\n100\t`BaseHTTPMiddleware` stack). Per the task constraint I did **not** weaken AC16 or\n101\tfabricate a pass — the perf test still asserts correctness and records the real\n102\tp95 (`meets_documented_budget: false`). The budget-number decision (plan Open\n103\tQuestion 1) is the human's: confirming 500 ms as binding at the 100k cap would\n104\trequire a **redesign** (e.g. C-accelerated/precomputed CSV materialization, or a\n105\tlower row cap, or moving the export off the `BaseHTTPMiddleware` request path) —\n106\tthat is a planning-escalation question, not a patch. This remediation delivers\n107\tthe ~7–17x reduction and removes the pathological anti-pattern; the residual\n108\tgap to 500 ms is the escalation.\n109\t\n110\t### Dead ends / notes\n111\t- First hypotheses (encoding-only; ASGI-framing-only) were **wrong** in\n112\t  isolation — each was < 0.5 s alone. The amplifier was the middleware × chunk\n113\t  count interaction, invisible unless the full middleware stack is in the path\n114\t  (minimal-app benchmark showed only ~1.6 s; the 4-layer benchmark reproduced ~7 s;\n115\t  the real app with real per-chunk middleware work + Argon2 auth reproduced ~10 s).\n116\t"}]},"uuid":"971860e1-cdb3-4341-b998-9c16718c653d","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:35:36.958Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ccf71612-0c92-4549-9df9-c6b5448b534a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
