{"parentUuid":"2443e530-ec07-4d03-82b0-561403a77c90","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs8F7BBbG9M4iJQhkxxx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012nGKkpTRQc4j3PsS3Q1Cfi","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2649,"cache_read_input_tokens":107215,"output_tokens":327,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2649},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":327,"cache_read_input_tokens":107215,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2649,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2649,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs8F5XDNSUkhcBeGb7F4","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"decf43a2-2e71-40f1-b0ee-0afdf498e268","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:36:48.448Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"decf43a2-2e71-40f1-b0ee-0afdf498e268","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012nGKkpTRQc4j3PsS3Q1Cfi","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Meterly\n2\t\n3\tUsage-metering ingestion API. See `PROJECT.md` for the product spec and\n4\t`docs/system_architecture.md` for the implementation overview.\n5\t\n6\t## Quickstart\n7\t\n8\t```bash\n9\tpoetry install\n10\tpoetry run alembic upgrade head\n11\tpoetry run uvicorn src.main:app --port 8000\n12\t```\n13\t\n14\t`GET /health` returns 200 with no dependencies (liveness). `GET /health/ready`\n15\tchecks the database connection and migration head (readiness).\n16\t"}]},"uuid":"12f4e378-e1f8-4e75-bde4-a628e6757517","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:36:48.494Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"decf43a2-2e71-40f1-b0ee-0afdf498e268","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"12f4e378-e1f8-4e75-bde4-a628e6757517","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs8FTurihuGF3EQatY6x","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":523,"cache_read_input_tokens":109864,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":523,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs8FStqYYaevRa7PajQy","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"280645a8-4ace-45ff-9314-10cf2e86741f","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:36:52.380Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"280645a8-4ace-45ff-9314-10cf2e86741f","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs8FTurihuGF3EQatY6x","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016Fe2YkuuAyxGjZh7HhGcMX","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\system_architecture.md","old_string":"**`GET /v1/usage/export` p95 measurement vs. the documented 500ms target\n(plan §\"Open questions\" #1, unresolved — flagged, not silently accepted).**\n`tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` measures real p95 latency for\na full 100,000-row export end to end (real Postgres testcontainer, in-process\nASGI transport) rather than asserting the documented 500ms budget, per the\nproject's existing honest-disclosure convention\n(`tests/integration/test_perf_smoke.py`). The measured p95 in this sandboxed\ndev environment was **~9.8 seconds** — far outside the documented 500ms\ntarget, driven by per-row Python-level CSV encoding/formatting/escaping and\ngenerator overhead across 100,000 rows, not primarily DB query time (the\npre-flight `COUNT` and the bounded 100k-row sort are both fast). This is a\nreal architectural cost of the per-row stdlib-`csv` streaming design the plan\nchose (constant memory, single DB snapshot) traded against raw throughput at\nthe row cap; it is not an artifact of this specific sandboxed run alone. The\nplan explicitly left the 500ms number as an *open, unconfirmed* target\npending checkpoint confirmation — this measurement is the data point that\nconfirms or adjusts it. Follow-up options if 500ms is confirmed as binding:\nbatch multiple rows per `csv.writer` flush, or reconsider the per-row\nescape/format call overhead; out of scope for this slice to change\nunilaterally since the plan fixed the streaming design.","new_string":"**`GET /v1/usage/export` p95 at the 100,000-row cap — resolved (was: plan\n§\"Open questions\" #1, originally unconfirmed).** The first measured p95\n(~10.7s locally / 25.2s on testing's independent re-measure) was root-caused\nduring debugging to the streaming generator yielding **one chunk per row**:\nthe app's four nested `BaseHTTPMiddleware` layers (`src/main.py`) each\nre-pump every streamed chunk through their own anyio memory-object-stream, so\ncost scaled with `chunk_count x middleware_layers` and dominated wall-clock\ntime at the 100k-row cap — not CSV encoding or DB query time, which were both\nsub-second in isolation. Three within-design fixes closed the gap (see\n`.pipeline/debug-notes.md` for the full isolation profiling):\n- `src/services/usage_export_service.py` batches `_ROWS_PER_CHUNK = 1000`\n  encoded rows per yielded chunk (was one row per chunk) — the primary lever,\n  cutting chunk count ~1,000x at the cap while staying constant-memory (the\n  buffer holds at most one batch).\n- `src/api/csv_export.py`'s `escape_csv_text_cell` replaced its per-character\n  strip loop with a precompiled `str.translate` deletion table (semantics\n  verified identical across all C0/DEL codepoints).\n- `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`'s `stream_usage_rollups` tunes the\n  server-side cursor with `execution_options(yield_per=_STREAM_FETCH_BATCH)`\n  (`_STREAM_FETCH_BATCH = 5000`) — more rows fetched per DB round-trip,\n  cursor still never abandoned.\n\nNet effect: p95 dropped from ~10.7s to a stable **p95 ~1.6-2.1s** (10-sample\nmeasurement). The original 500ms target proved unreachable within the\napproved constant-memory-streaming design (an irreducible ~0.85-1.0s floor\nfrom the server-side cursor drain + per-row CSV encoding, even discounting\nmiddleware). The human confirmed a revised, binding budget of **p95 <=\n3,000ms at the 100,000-row cap** at the 2026-07-09 escalation, which\n`tests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py` now hard-asserts (AC16); this\nsession's re-run measured p95 1,643.87ms, comfortably under the bound."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":523,"cache_read_input_tokens":109864,"output_tokens":1734,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":523},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1734,"cache_read_input_tokens":109864,"cache_creation_input_tokens":523,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":523,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs8FStqYYaevRa7PajQy","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"ef9bf5bd-fa94-47de-94fc-5075b556ec3e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:37:06.188Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
