{"parentUuid":"1ccff376-96cd-46d8-a535-0aa2202047f1","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs8HCB7kVWunZnRA2ucE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, that's the only remaining reference and it's now correctly framed as historical context. Now let's verify test locations README (tests/ directories) since new test files were added there."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":310,"cache_read_input_tokens":112222,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":310,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs8HAxCKjJwZEPNLxPuY","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"898b33f4-aa61-46d3-bb28-74ddad7c17b3","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:37:13.943Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"898b33f4-aa61-46d3-bb28-74ddad7c17b3","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs8HCB7kVWunZnRA2ucE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0184Sj5oLTaD9xDeDRT9AtLr","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":310,"cache_read_input_tokens":112222,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":310,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs8HAxCKjJwZEPNLxPuY","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"01df742f-25a1-4066-a701-f797d1686236","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:37:14.664Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"01df742f-25a1-4066-a701-f797d1686236","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0184Sj5oLTaD9xDeDRT9AtLr","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# tests/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tUnit and fast component tests (no live Postgres/Redis) for the `src/` package,\n6\tplus the `tests/integration/` suite (real Postgres/Redis via testcontainers,\n7\tand real HTTP/k6 load). Mirrors `src/`'s layering: schema/crypto/time-window\n8\tunit tests here, endpoint/migration/concurrency/perf tests under `integration/`.\n9\t\n10\t## Modules\n11\t\n12\t| File | Responsibility |\n13\t|---|---|\n14\t| `conftest.py` | Shared fixtures for the non-integration suite. |\n15\t| `test_app_smoke.py` | App-construction-level tests needing no DB/Redis: liveness, OpenAPI exposure, unauthenticated-denial/error-envelope shape. |\n16\t| `test_auth_api_key.py` | Split-token parsing and the in-process verification cache (Argon2id-vs-p95 cache mechanism). |\n17\t| `test_crypto.py` | `src/crypto` facade: Argon2id hash/verify, constant-time compare. |\n18\t| `test_dast_context_documented.py` | Asserts the DAST scanner auth context (header + token shape) is documented somewhere a DAST job's config can read it. |\n19\t| `test_db_session_isolation.py` | Regression guard for the `READ COMMITTED` isolation pin in `src/db/session.py` — the dependency the quota lock-then-read atomicity in `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::read_tenant_quota_state_locked` relies on. |\n20\t| `test_dependency_pins.py` | Security-regression guard against a starlette CVE-carrying downgrade (pinned version stays at the patched release). |\n21\t| `test_logging_redaction.py` | A raw `customer_id` (or other sensitive field) must never reach the rendered log line regardless of call site. |\n22\t| `test_rate_limit_fail_open.py` | Regression test for the Tier-2 rate-limit logging facade in `src/auth/rate_limit.py`. |\n23\t| `test_schemas_events.py` | Validation-contract tests for `EventCreateRequest`. |\n24\t| `test_schemas_quotas.py` | Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (anchored `customer_id`/`metric` allowlists, `limit_per_window` bounds, injection rejection). |\n25\t| `test_schemas_usage.py` | Validation-contract tests for `UsageQueryParams`. |\n26\t| `test_slo_alarms_defined.py` | Static assertion that the declared SLO burn-rate + canary CloudWatch alarms exist in the Terraform source with the exact names `deploy.yml` expects. |\n27\t| `test_time_windows.py` | Tests for the UTC hour-flooring helper (`window_start_utc`) shared by `events_service`, `usage_service`, and `quota_service`. |\n28\t| `integration/` | Tests requiring a real Postgres/Redis (testcontainers) or a live HTTP process — see `tests/integration/README.md`. |\n29\t\n30\t## Relationships\n31\t\n32\t- Unit tests here import directly from `src.*` modules (schemas, crypto, auth, time\n33\t  windows) with no network/DB dependency — fast, run on every commit.\n34\t- `integration/` depends on Docker (testcontainers for Postgres/Redis, and for\n35\t  `test_perf_k6_load.py`, the `grafana/k6` image) and is slower; both suites are\n36\t  collected together by `pytest --cov=src --cov-branch` (per `CLAUDE.md`).\n37\t- Test IDs referenced in docstrings (`AC1`, `AC-PERF`, etc.) trace to\n38\t  `.pipeline/acceptance.md`'s acceptance criteria for the feature that introduced them.\n39\t"}]},"uuid":"a1009934-3e33-4392-92e5-882ba3e77148","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:37:14.681Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"01df742f-25a1-4066-a701-f797d1686236","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"a1009934-3e33-4392-92e5-882ba3e77148","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs8HCB7kVWunZnRA2ucE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011Y27Nf1BrJn9kHvK5XKV6X","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":310,"cache_read_input_tokens":112222,"output_tokens":229,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":310},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":229,"cache_read_input_tokens":112222,"cache_creation_input_tokens":310,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":310,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs8HAxCKjJwZEPNLxPuY","attributionAgent":"documentation","type":"assistant","uuid":"994fc018-56c4-406b-9625-2d57227e7cde","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:37:15.174Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"994fc018-56c4-406b-9625-2d57227e7cde","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"795b6292-899f-43d1-822d-8e0cc35d6b7d","agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011Y27Nf1BrJn9kHvK5XKV6X","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# tests/integration/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tIntegration tests that exercise the app against real dependencies: Postgres and\n6\tRedis via testcontainers, a live out-of-process uvicorn for perf/load tests, and\n7\tAlembic migrations run against a scratch database. Complements the fast unit\n8\tsuite in `tests/` (no live DB/Redis there).\n9\t\n10\t## Modules\n11\t\n12\t| File | Responsibility |\n13\t|---|---|\n14\t| `conftest.py` | Shared fixtures: testcontainer Postgres/Redis setup, the FastAPI test client, seeded `api_keys` rows. |\n15\t| `test_concurrency.py` | 50 concurrent same-`idempotency_key` POSTs create exactly one `events` row (idempotency under concurrency). |\n16\t| `test_data_protection.py` | `api_keys.secret_hash` is persisted as an Argon2id hash, never plaintext; the normal auth path still verifies end to end. |\n17\t| `test_events_endpoint.py` | `POST /v1/events` integration tests (create, replay, validation, auth). |\n18\t| `test_events_quota_enforcement.py` | `POST /v1/events` quota-check integration tests: unlimited-without-a-quota, under/at/over-limit, replay-bypasses-quota, mid-window quota change, throttle-vs-quota distinct error codes. |\n19\t| `test_health_readiness.py` | `/health/ready` against a live, migrated Postgres. |\n20\t| `test_migrations.py` | Migration round-trip (`0001`/`0002`) on a prod-shaped seeded dataset, own scratch testcontainer. |\n21\t| `test_perf_k6_load.py` | Sustained k6 load (via Docker) against a real out-of-process uvicorn; drives both the no-quota baseline and the quota-active scenario at equal worker budget for the AC20 relative p95 comparison. |\n22\t| `test_perf_smoke.py` | Smoke-sized perf check (no k6/Locust dependency) against a live uvicorn process. |\n23\t| `test_quota_concurrency.py` | N concurrent distinct-`idempotency_key` posts against a quota cap `L` never drive the rollup total above `L` (`FOR UPDATE` row-lock serialization proof). |\n24\t| `test_quota_migration.py` | Migration `0003` (`quotas` table + `api_keys.scope`) round-trip and constraint re-enforcement. |\n25\t| `test_quotas_endpoint.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` integration tests: create/replace, auth, admin-scope enforcement, validation, tenant isolation, rate limiting, OpenAPI exposure. |\n26\t| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. |\n27\t| `test_rate_limit.py` | Tier-2 (`api_key_id`-keyed) rate limiting: two principals on one IP get independent buckets; one principal across two IPs shares one bucket. |\n28\t| `test_seed_api_key_script.py` | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` provisions a key against a real database, including the `--admin` flag setting `scope='admin'` (default `scope='ingest'`). |\n29\t| `test_usage_endpoint.py` | `GET /v1/usage` integration tests (aggregation, tenant isolation). |\n30\t| `k6/` | k6 load-test scripts driven by `test_perf_k6_load.py` — see `k6/README.md`. |\n31\t\n32\t## Relationships\n33\t\n34\t- All DB-backed tests share the Postgres/Redis testcontainer fixtures from `conftest.py`,\n35\t  except `test_migrations.py` and `test_quota_migration.py`, which own a scratch\n36\t  testcontainer independently (they drive the migration lifecycle itself: down to a\n37\t  prior revision and back up, which the shared fixture's already-migrated database\n38\t  can't support).\n39\t- `test_perf_k6_load.py` and `k6/load_events_quota.js` work as a pair: the Python test\n40\t  starts uvicorn, seeds fixture data (including quota rows for the quota-active run),\n41\t  invokes the k6 script via Docker, and asserts against the JSON summary it produces.\n42\t- Docstring AC references (`AC7`, `AC13`, `AC16`, `AC20`, etc.) trace to\n43\t  `.pipeline/acceptance.md`.\n44\t"}]},"uuid":"ea277d36-861f-496b-9a10-8afa5f4e13ed","timestamp":"2026-07-09T20:37:15.200Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"994fc018-56c4-406b-9625-2d57227e7cde","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
