{"parentUuid":"fc87d51b-221a-4d92-9fa4-2571d63cb785","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adbf605e02d6e3dc5","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs8UvvBQpmRcv7av4Prj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Documentation pass complete. Summary of what was done:\n\n**Gates confirmed clean:** `.pipeline/security-report.md` (status: clean) and `.pipeline/test-results.json` (status: pass, 180/180).\n\n**Directories touched by this diff, READMEs updated:**\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\README.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\README.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\README.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\README.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\README.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\system_architecture.md`\n\n**Identifier corrections found and fixed (verified against source, not recalled)** — these were pre-existing errors in the README files this pass touches:\n- `src/services/README.md`: `usage_service.py`'s `read_usage(...)` → real name is `get_usage(principal, query)`; `time_windows.py`'s `window_start_utc` → real name is `floor_to_hour_utc`.\n- `src/repositories/README.md`: `events_repo.py`'s `create_or_replay_event(...)` / `upsert_rollup()` → real functions are `insert_event_if_new`, `find_event_by_idempotency_key`, `increment_usage_rollup`.\n- `src/api/README.md`: `usage_service.read_usage` reference fixed to `get_usage`; `get_app()` (nonexistent) fixed to the real `create_app()` in `src/main.py`.\n\nAll new usage-export identifiers (`prepare_export`, `stream_export_csv`, `count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`, `UsageRollupExportRecord`, `escape_csv_text_cell`, `UsageExportQueryParams`, `_ROWS_PER_CHUNK`, `yield_per`, etc.) were grepped/read at their def sites and matched the docs exactly — no invented names introduced.\n\n`docs/system_architecture.md`: replaced the stale \"p95 ~9.8s, unresolved\" section with the resolved cycle-2 remediation narrative (root cause, three fixes, human-confirmed 3,000ms budget, measured 1,643.87ms). The Mermaid flow diagram already covered the export path from a prior pass, so it was left as-is.\n\nRoot `README.md` and `PROJECT.md` setup/run/deploy steps were unaffected — not touched.\n\n**Design-record retention:** copied `plan.md`, `acceptance.md`, `plan-audit.md`, `security-report.md`, `run-summary.json` into `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\decisions\\feature\\usage-export\\` (no `design-spec.md` — this feature's `design_source: none`). Scanned copies for credential-shaped strings — clean.\n\n**PR description** written to `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\pr-description.md`, reporting the acceptance-criteria split as **21 test-covered + 1 delegated to security (AC18)**, branch coverage (66%), the advisory test-quality signal (mutation unmeasured on Windows, adversarial gaps), a Supply chain section (lockfile clean, SBOM 65 components), and an advisory DAST (runtime) section (target reached, 0 high/3 medium/4 low, none over budget). No Assurance note or Design review section was needed (assurance is `\"standard\"`; no design source was used this run, so no design-review skip disclosure applies either).\n\n**Reviewed-state hash** recorded last, after all doc edits: `.pipeline/review-manifest.json` → `reviewed_change_hash=eb52dff6c8ea72b115ad1a067ac911cf52939152db601db32d7c8c691748b7fa`."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":182,"cache_read_input_tokens":131026,"output_tokens":1468,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch